FBIS4-29180 "dreas116__a94017" FBIS-EAS-94-116-A Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 ANNEX Japan Continued Reportage on Reaction to DPRK Issues Continued Reportage on Reaction to DPRK Issues SDPJ Chairman Comments OW1506225594 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 15 Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW1506225594 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database Japanese BFN [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 15 Jun Morning Edition] [Text] The DPRK (North Korea) has declared its withdrawal from the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA). Concerning this fact, the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] announced on 14 June a statement in the name of Chairman Tomiichi Murayama, which reads: "From our standpoint of turning Northeast Asia into a nuclear-free zone and of achieving peace and prosperity in this region through international cooperation, we would like to express our regret."
